{% if customer_facing_ai %}
### Consumer Law Risk

{{ business_name }} uses AI to generate customer-facing content. Under the **Australian Consumer Law (ACL)**:

- **Section 18** (misleading conduct) is **strict liability** — no intent required.
- If AI generates inaccurate product claims, pricing, or recommendations, the organisation is liable.
{% if ai_generated_content_reviewed %}
- **Mitigation**: Human review is in place before publication.
{% else %}
- **ACTION REQUIRED**: No human review process exists. This exposes the organisation to ACL penalties of up to **$50 million**.
{% endif %}
{% endif %}

