## 6. Director Liability Considerations

Directors should be aware of:

- **Corporations Act s180**: Duty of care requires being informed about AI risks.
- **Section 16C Privacy Act**: Vicarious liability for overseas AI vendor breaches.
- **Statutory Tort**: Any organisation (regardless of size) can be sued for serious privacy invasions.
{% if customer_facing_ai %}
- **ACL Strict Liability**: No intent required for misleading AI-generated customer content.
{% endif %}

Regular board briefings on AI governance (recommended quarterly) demonstrate due diligence and reduce personal liability risk.

